"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">12</A>
<I>i.e.</I> chaos: <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">antiqui</SPAN> <I>sc.</I> <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">mundi</SPAN>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note13" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Aetna/text*.html#ref13
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">13</A>
Ellis justifiably defended this line against attack, <I>Jrnl. Philol.</I> <SPAN CLASS="small">XVI</SPAN>.301<!--</A>JOURNAL-->, citing the parallel doctrine of Seneca,
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/sen/sen.qn2.shtml
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(EClickHere+'Seneca\'s Natural Questions'+Lat2+LatSearch+'agitatus</SPAN>',WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<I>Nat. Quaest.</I> <SPAN CLASS="small">II</SPAN>.<SPAN CLASS="smaller">I</SPAN>.3
	</A>
(<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">cum motus terrae fiat spiritu, spiritus autem sit aer agitatus . . .</SPAN>): <SPAN CLASS="small">VI</SPAN>.<SPAN CLASS="smaller">XXI</SPAN> and <SPAN CLASS="smaller">XXII</SPAN>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note14" HREF="
